# Allowlist for check-empty-where-on-mutation.ts (PR-R1-15)
#
# Format (fingerprint, line-shift-resilient):
#   <file> <8-hex-fingerprint>  # <preview> | BUG-XXX — <reason>
#
# Each entry grants amnesty for a specific UPDATE/DELETE chain that
# intentionally omits a WHERE clause (e.g., admin factory-reset flows,
# scheduled-job global-clear operations, audit purges).
#
# Cascade-tracking: every entry should cite a BUG-ID. PR-R1-15 baseline
# drain tracked under BUG-PR-R1-15-CASCADE-DRAIN-EMPTY-WHERE.
# Expiry-policy: per-entry (added 2026-05-03 cycle Phase 0a.7)
# Each non-comment line carries an `| expires: <YYYY-MM-DD> (cascade: <BUG>)`
# OR `| permanent: <reason>` annotation. Entries past their expiry date
# fail the merge gate via `scripts/guards/check-allowlist-expiry.ts`.
# Renewal: when a target close-by date passes, EITHER drain the entry
# (preferred) OR explicitly extend the date with operator authorization.
